race.comment: VIVIAN'S EXPRESS (3) opened this prep with a couple of nice efforts then tackled the Vo Rogue at Group 3 level last start and was no match for Ninja and others. Given a five-week let-up and drops significantly in grade. Big chance to hit form with the help of an ideal gate. CHIX (4) went to Randwick last start after a win on debut but wasn't up to the task and was slow to recover. Freshened up and kept up to the mark with a subsequent trial. Big chance to turn things around. YOU'RE THE CHOICE (9) returned from a 20-week spell with an effortless all-the-way win over this trip at Gosford recently. Yet to prove herself more than one run into a prep but the ease of that latest win is hard to ignore. PELOSA (2) returns from a 38-week lay-off. Ran a decent race here first-up last prep then went on to miss narrowly in town two runs later. Three trials since 9 December will have her forward enough.
